x > -1
\arctan x + \arctan\dfrac{1-x}{1+x} = \dfrac{\pi}{4} 
x
x=0
\arctan(x) = a
x>-1
a = \arctan(x) \in \left(-\dfrac{\pi}4, \dfrac{\pi}2 \right)
\dfrac{\pi}4 - a \in \left(-\dfrac{\pi}4, \dfrac{\pi}2 \right) \implies \arctan \left(\tan(\pi/4-a)\right) = \dfrac{\pi}4-a
(x,y)\in\text{a suitable set}
 \arctan x + \arctan y = \arctan \frac{x+y}{1-xy} 
